g/75px-Speech_balloon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Speech_balloon.svg/100px-Speech_balloon.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"525\" data-file-height=\"425\" /></a><div style=\"padding-top:0.2em;line-height:1.2em\"><a href=\"/wiki/Speech_balloon\" title=\"Speech balloon\">Speech balloons</a></div></td></tr><tr><th style=\"padding:0.1em;background:antiquewhite;\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Comics_studies\" title=\"Comics studies\">Comics studies</a></th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em\">\n<ul><li><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Education</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/History_of_comics\" title=\"History of comics\">History</a>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Comics_by_country\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Comics by country\">by country</a></li></ul></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Glossary_of_comics_terminology\" title=\"Glossary of comics terminology\">Glossary</a></li></ul></td>\n</tr><tr><th style=\"padding:0.1em;background:antiquewhite;\">\nMethods</th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Cartoonist\" title=\"Cartoonist\">Cartooning</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Photo_comics\" title=\"Photo comics\">Fumetti</a></li></ul></td>\n</tr><tr><th style=\"padding:0.1em;background:antiquewhite;\">\nMedia</th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Comic_book\" title=\"Comic book\">Comic book</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Comic_strip\" title=\"Comic strip\">Comic strip</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Editorial_cartoon\" title=\"Editorial cartoon\">Editorial cartoon</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Gag_cartoon\" title=\"Gag cartoon\">Gag cartoon</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Graphic_novel\" title=\"Graphic novel\">Graphic novel</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Manga\" title=\"Manga\">Manga</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Webcomic\" title=\"Webcomic\">Webcomic</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Webtoon\" title=\"Webtoon\">Webtoon</a></li></ul></td>\n</tr><tr><th style=\"padding:0.1em;background:antiquewhite;\">\nCommunity</th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Comics_artist\" title=\"Comics artist\">Artists</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/List_of_comics_awards\" title=\"List of comics awards\">Awards</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Cartoonist\" title=\"Cartoonist\">Cartoonist</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Comic_book_collecting\" title=\"Comic book collecting\">Collecting</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/List_of_comics_publishing_companies\" title=\"List of comics publishing companies\">Publishers</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/List_of_best-selling_comic_series\" title=\"List of best-selling comic series\">Sales</a></li></ul></td>\n</tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0.3em 0.4em 0.3em;font-weight:bold;background:antiquewhite;\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Speech_balloon.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Speech balloon.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Speech_balloon.svg/32px-Speech_balloon.svg.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"26\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Speech_balloon.svg/48px-Speech_balloon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Speech_balloon.svg/64px-Speech_balloon.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"525\" data-file-height=\"425\" /></a> <a href=\"/wiki/Portal:Comics\" title=\"Portal:Comics\">Comics&#32;portal</a></td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align:right;font-size:115%\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Comics_navbar\" title=\"Template:Comics navbar\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Comics_navbar\" title=\"Template talk:Comics navbar\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\">t</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Comics_navbar&amp;action=edit\"><abbr title=\"Edit this template\">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The use of <b>comics in education</b> is based on the concept of creating engagement and motivation for students. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Overview\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Overview</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Further_reading\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Further reading</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Overview\">Overview</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Comics_in_education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Overview\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The effectiveness of comics as medium for effective learning and development has been the subject of debate since the origin modern comic book in the 1930s.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Sones (1944) notes that comics \"evoked more than a hundred critical articles in educational and non-professional periodicals.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The use of comics in education would later attract the attention of <a href=\"/wiki/Fredric_Wertham\" title=\"Fredric Wertham\">Fredric Wertham</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> who noted that the use of comics in education represented \"an all-time low in American science.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dorrell1995_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dorrell1995-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>It has been noted that the use of a narrative form such as a comic \"can foster pupils' interest in science\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> and help students remember what they have learnt<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> and providing a means of fostering discussion.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dorrell1995_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dorrell1995-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> However, it has also been noted that many educators remain \"ambivalent\" about the use of comic books as an educational tool.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> Comics have also been used as a medium to communicate health care information on subjects such as diabetes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the USA, the use of comics for education, using the Internet, can be seen on <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://comicsintheclassroom.net\">Comics in the Classroom</a>, and the state of Maryland's <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20080511164542/http://www.marylandpublicschools.org/MSDE/programs/recognition-partnerships/md-comic-book.htm\">Comic Book Initiative</a>. Teacher professional development content on how teachers can integrate comics into the classroom is available through the State of California Department of Education's Brokers of Expertis website.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Comics_in_education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Comics_studies\" title=\"Comics studies\">Comics studies</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Comics_in_education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Gruenberg, S (1944). \"The Comics as a Social Force\". <i>Journal of Educational Sociology</i>. American Sociological Association. <b>18</b> (4): 204\u2013213. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.2307/2262693\">10.2307/2262693</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/JSTOR\" title=\"JSTOR\">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.jstor.org/stable/2262693\">2262693</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Educational+Sociology&amp;rft.atitle=The+Comics+as+a+Social+Force&amp;rft.volume=18&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.pages=204-213&amp;rft.date=1944&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.2307%2F2262693&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F2262693&amp;rft.aulast=Gruenberg&amp;rft.aufirst=S&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AComics+in+education\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Hutchinson, K (1949). \"An experiment in the use of comics as instructional material\". <i>Journal of Educational Sociology</i>. American Sociological Association. <b>23</b> (4): 236\u2013245. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.2307/2264559\">10.2307/2264559</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/JSTOR\" title=\"JSTOR\">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.jstor.org/stable/2264559\">2264559</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Educational+Sociology&amp;rft.atitle=An+experiment+in+the+use+of+comics+as+instructional+material&amp;rft.volume=23&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.pages=236-245&amp;rft.date=1949&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.2307%2F2264559&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F2264559&amp;rft.aulast=Hutchinson&amp;rft.aufirst=K&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AComics+in+education\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Sones, W (1944). \"The comics and instructional method\". <i>Journal of Educational Sociology</i>. American Sociological A